1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:04,462
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:09,884 --> 00:00:10,719
‪[electronic blipping]

3
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:18,601
[Atoy] <i>Hurry, hurry! Chase them, Karla!</i>

4
00:00:19,352 --> 00:00:24,524
Please have mercy on me! Let me go!

5
00:00:24,607 --> 00:00:26,860
[driver, in English] Boss…
Someone's following us.

6
00:00:26,943 --> 00:00:29,696
[in English] What are you waiting for?
Shoot them!

7
00:00:29,779 --> 00:00:32,532
[Tonet] <i>Until now,</i>
<i>Atoy and Karla still have not shown up.</i>

8
00:00:32,615 --> 00:00:33,867
‪-[Karla gasps]
‪-[Atoy groans]

9
00:00:33,950 --> 00:00:35,535
[Tonet] <i>Do you know where they auditioned?</i>

10
00:00:35,618 --> 00:00:36,453
‪[man grunts]

11
00:00:36,536 --> 00:00:38,496
[Ibyang, in English] <i>Au… Audition?</i>

12
00:00:38,580 --> 00:00:39,748
[Tonet] <i>Why, Ibyang?</i>

13
00:00:39,831 --> 00:00:41,624
Did they not audition?

14
00:00:41,708 --> 00:00:43,334
[Ibyang, in English] <i>Protect their steps,</i>

15
00:00:43,418 --> 00:00:46,379
<i>guide their path,</i>
<i>and bring them home safely.</i>

16
00:00:48,006 --> 00:00:51,760
- [Ame shrieks]
- [Red] <i>That bastard. He ruined the plan.</i>

17
00:00:52,260 --> 00:00:55,305
I hope I see them again,
so I can make them crawl to hell.

18
00:00:55,889 --> 00:00:58,683
- [Ibyang] <i>Sis Ame!</i>
- [Tonet] <i>Is that his job?</i>

19
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:00,101
[Tonet] <i>Are they undercover police?</i>

20
00:01:00,185 --> 00:01:02,270
It really is not allowed, sis.
Just ignore it.

21
00:01:02,353 --> 00:01:05,065
No, I really cannot settle down.

22
00:01:05,148 --> 00:01:07,108
[Cita] <i>He was formerly in the military.</i>

23
00:01:07,192 --> 00:01:10,653
<i>That is where he was trained</i>
<i>in combat for a long time.</i>

24
00:01:10,737 --> 00:01:14,115
<i>One of his areas of expertise</i>
<i>is finding people,</i>

25
00:01:14,199 --> 00:01:16,910
<i>and until now, he still uses it.</i>

26
00:01:16,993 --> 00:01:18,578
[Ibyang, in English] <i>Goodbye,</i>
<i>Master Grumpy!</i>

27
00:01:18,661 --> 00:01:20,622
[Ibyang] Thank you for all of your help.

28
00:01:20,705 --> 00:01:23,374
But I hope this is our last meeting.

29
00:01:23,458 --> 00:01:24,667
[man] <i>Entry is no longer allowed here.</i>

30
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:26,544
<i>This is now a private property.</i>

31
00:01:26,628 --> 00:01:28,254
[Atoy] <i>I will give you tenfold of that</i>

32
00:01:28,338 --> 00:01:30,548
<i>if you can tell me where I can find them.</i>

33
00:01:30,632 --> 00:01:33,384
[man] <i>I will call my friends,</i>
<i>so we can easily find Ame.</i>

34
00:01:43,061 --> 00:01:44,229
[Martina, in English] Who is that?

35
00:01:45,230 --> 00:01:47,649
The old person who caused trouble
at Endless Nights last night.

36
00:01:49,150 --> 00:01:50,443
So, what is he?

37
00:01:50,527 --> 00:01:52,320
Police? Military?

38
00:01:54,572 --> 00:01:56,616
That is what I am asking
my people to find out.

39
00:01:56,699 --> 00:01:59,035
[inquisitive music playing]

40
00:01:59,911 --> 00:02:02,372
We do not even know
if that is his real name.

41
00:02:04,916 --> 00:02:06,417
[Martina, in English] Relax.

42
00:02:06,501 --> 00:02:09,879
From your story,
it does not seem like you were the target.

43
00:02:09,963 --> 00:02:11,506
[in English] Seems like
he was after the midget.

44
00:02:13,424 --> 00:02:15,260
I am a silent partner in Endless Nights.

45
00:02:17,011 --> 00:02:20,390
Now it is closed
and being investigated by the police.

46
00:02:20,473 --> 00:02:22,976
I am losing a lot of money
because of that old man.

47
00:02:24,435 --> 00:02:26,646
I need to know where he is connected,

48
00:02:28,314 --> 00:02:30,650
so I can prepare for our confrontation.

49
00:02:33,778 --> 00:02:39,159
[inquisitive music continues]

50
00:02:42,453 --> 00:02:44,747
Godmother, nothing.
They are not at the terminal.

51
00:02:44,831 --> 00:02:48,501
And the people I asked who knew them

52
00:02:48,585 --> 00:02:51,462
also have not seen them
and do not know where they went.

53
00:02:51,546 --> 00:02:55,466
You let them leave last night.

54
00:02:55,550 --> 00:02:59,846
Godmother, you know
they insisted on leaving.

55
00:03:00,555 --> 00:03:02,557
Besides, this is just
one piece of clothing.

56
00:03:02,640 --> 00:03:06,561
Atoy, the child's clothes
are no longer the issue here.

57
00:03:06,644 --> 00:03:09,188
[scoffs] You did not even think about it.

58
00:03:09,272 --> 00:03:11,649
Are you not worried
where the two slept last night?

59
00:03:11,733 --> 00:03:14,110
[somber music playing]

60
00:03:14,193 --> 00:03:18,114
Since you are already there,
continue looking for Ibyang.

61
00:03:18,197 --> 00:03:21,534
What if the people looking for Ame
come back for them?

62
00:03:21,618 --> 00:03:22,952
Have you thought about that?

63
00:03:23,036 --> 00:03:26,247
[Cita] <i>What if something bad happens</i>
<i>to the two of them?</i>

64
00:03:27,332 --> 00:03:28,958
All right, all right,
I will look for them.

65
00:03:29,834 --> 00:03:30,877
Okay, Godmother.

66
00:03:33,713 --> 00:03:37,675
[unsettling music playing]

67
00:03:37,759 --> 00:03:38,885
‪[indistinct chattering]

68
00:03:56,527 --> 00:03:57,862
‪[sauve music playing]

69
00:04:22,679 --> 00:04:25,348
I am getting hungry, sis.

70
00:04:25,431 --> 00:04:28,226
Tell your stomach to wait.

71
00:04:28,309 --> 00:04:31,104
We still need to find a place to get food.

72
00:04:32,230 --> 00:04:36,734
We were already in a house
with a big fridge,

73
00:04:36,818 --> 00:04:38,194
and you still wanted to leave.

74
00:04:38,278 --> 00:04:42,949
There you go, Sis Ame is blaming again.

75
00:04:43,032 --> 00:04:45,785
I just do not want to see Master Grumpy!

76
00:04:45,868 --> 00:04:49,539
You are the only one
who thinks he is grumpy.

77
00:04:49,622 --> 00:04:51,082
He is actually very impressive.

78
00:04:51,165 --> 00:04:54,502
He saved me. He risked his own life.

79
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:57,547
[in English] He is my hero.

80
00:04:57,630 --> 00:05:01,592
[dreamy music playing]

81
00:05:03,344 --> 00:05:04,304
‪[Vladimir shouts]

82
00:05:06,431 --> 00:05:07,640
‪[sensual musical sting]

83
00:05:07,724 --> 00:05:09,142
Ame…

84
00:05:10,935 --> 00:05:12,270
Are you okay?

85
00:05:12,353 --> 00:05:16,316
[cheeky music playing]

86
00:05:24,449 --> 00:05:25,408
Sis Ame?

87
00:05:25,992 --> 00:05:27,535
Sis Ame!

88
00:05:27,618 --> 00:05:28,953
What happened to you?

89
00:05:29,037 --> 00:05:30,955
[cheeky music playing]

90
00:05:31,039 --> 00:05:33,708
Maybe we should just go back
to Atoy's house.

91
00:05:33,791 --> 00:05:35,001
We can eat there.

92
00:05:35,877 --> 00:05:37,879
Sleep in his room.

93
00:05:39,047 --> 00:05:42,508
I really do not want to go back
to Master Grumpy!

94
00:05:43,342 --> 00:05:45,011
Are you really serious?

95
00:05:46,054 --> 00:05:47,555
You would rather let your pride win

96
00:05:47,638 --> 00:05:50,600
than listen to your growling stomach?

97
00:05:50,683 --> 00:05:52,894
- Come on, sis!
- [somber music playing]

98
00:05:52,977 --> 00:05:56,939
Let us stop arguing about Master Grumpy.

99
00:05:58,107 --> 00:06:01,110
Let us find food somewhere else.

100
00:06:04,405 --> 00:06:07,700
[Cita] <i>What if the person</i>
<i>looking for Ame comes back?</i>

101
00:06:07,784 --> 00:06:09,285
<i>Have you thought about that?</i>

102
00:06:12,121 --> 00:06:13,706
Ibyang?

103
00:06:13,790 --> 00:06:15,208
Ibyang!

104
00:06:15,291 --> 00:06:17,835
[car revving]

105
00:06:19,045 --> 00:06:20,880
Ibyang! What--

106
00:06:20,963 --> 00:06:22,298
Who is Ibyang?

107
00:06:25,802 --> 00:06:27,261
Are you okay? Are you okay?!

108
00:06:27,345 --> 00:06:30,890
Come on, kid. Next time, be more careful.

109
00:06:30,973 --> 00:06:33,351
- Okay, thank you.
- All right.

110
00:06:33,434 --> 00:06:35,561
[somber music continues]

111
00:06:45,822 --> 00:06:48,116
CONGEE
NOODLES

112
00:06:50,118 --> 00:06:53,246
Come on, Ibyang,
before the leftovers are cleared away.

113
00:06:53,329 --> 00:06:57,333
[cheeky music playing]

114
00:06:57,416 --> 00:06:58,584
[Ame] Hurry!

115
00:07:00,878 --> 00:07:02,296
This is delicious!

116
00:07:04,632 --> 00:07:06,175
Eat now!

117
00:07:12,932 --> 00:07:13,850
The soup is delicious.

118
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:15,852
This is salty.

119
00:07:15,935 --> 00:07:19,689
Ma'am, where did you buy this dumpling?

120
00:07:20,648 --> 00:07:22,442
It is tasty.

121
00:07:22,525 --> 00:07:25,319
Atoy bought that for you.

122
00:07:26,195 --> 00:07:28,865
Uh… It is so salty.

123
00:07:29,740 --> 00:07:30,741
Salty.

124
00:07:30,825 --> 00:07:33,161
Salty? But you almost finished it.

125
00:07:33,786 --> 00:07:34,704
Still salty.

126
00:07:43,671 --> 00:07:45,882
Why are you smiling there?

127
00:07:45,965 --> 00:07:47,467
You miss Atoy, right?

128
00:07:48,050 --> 00:07:49,677
No!

129
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:52,305
Why would I miss that grumpy one?

130
00:07:52,889 --> 00:07:54,182
Come on, eat!

131
00:07:55,766 --> 00:07:58,102
- Here, soup.
- Mmm.

132
00:07:58,186 --> 00:07:59,395
Hey!

133
00:08:00,062 --> 00:08:01,147
Why are you devouring my food?

134
00:08:01,230 --> 00:08:04,066
I just went to pee, and you attacked it!

135
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:06,152
You should have put it on reserve!

136
00:08:07,695 --> 00:08:08,696
Hey, the bag, the bag!

137
00:08:16,829 --> 00:08:19,290
[somber music playing]

138
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:24,879
Sis, my stomach is still growling.

139
00:08:26,631 --> 00:08:29,008
Are you sure you do not
want to go back to Atoy?

140
00:08:29,967 --> 00:08:36,516
[pensive music playing]

141
00:08:39,268 --> 00:08:40,102
Hello there!

142
00:08:40,186 --> 00:08:42,688
[in English] Ah, good morning!
How can I help you?

143
00:08:42,772 --> 00:08:44,273
Son of a thread.

144
00:08:44,357 --> 00:08:46,526
This is giving me a nosebleed.

145
00:08:46,609 --> 00:08:48,444
Hey, buddy, I also know
how to speak Tagalog.

146
00:08:48,528 --> 00:08:50,738
No nosebleed here!

147
00:08:50,821 --> 00:08:52,114
[in English] You want to try the pares?

148
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:53,407
Of course, this is delicious!

149
00:08:53,491 --> 00:08:55,451
- Ah, sure.
- Yeah.

150
00:08:56,285 --> 00:08:59,497
Ah, bro. Well, um, there is…

151
00:08:59,580 --> 00:09:01,415
I am looking for a child in your area.

152
00:09:01,999 --> 00:09:03,501
Her name is Ibyang.

153
00:09:03,584 --> 00:09:05,294
- Maybe you have seen her.
- Uh…

154
00:09:05,378 --> 00:09:08,965
She is usually with a little person,
who is also female.

155
00:09:09,048 --> 00:09:11,509
[in English] Ah, okay…
Do you have some pictures, maybe?

156
00:09:12,301 --> 00:09:14,637
Maybe I can post it here at my pares place

157
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:16,180
and on social media as well,

158
00:09:16,264 --> 00:09:19,350
and in my next vlog, I will ask people.

159
00:09:20,101 --> 00:09:23,980
I do not have any pictures
because I just recently met them.

160
00:09:24,063 --> 00:09:26,357
What social media do you have?
Where will you post it if ever?

161
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:28,025
Brother Kurt! On all of them.

162
00:09:28,109 --> 00:09:30,194
- Brother Kurt?
- Mmm-hmm.

163
00:09:30,278 --> 00:09:32,071
If ever you see them,

164
00:09:32,154 --> 00:09:34,615
- please post it or maybe give a shout-out.
- [in English] Okay.

165
00:09:35,199 --> 00:09:36,158
[Gavin] That's my first time.

166
00:09:36,242 --> 00:09:37,952
These two seem to like
hanging around our place.

167
00:09:38,035 --> 00:09:40,162
- [Karla] Who?
- [in English] I need a drink for this.

168
00:09:40,246 --> 00:09:41,664
- [in English] Right, bro.
- [in English] And fries.

169
00:09:43,499 --> 00:09:45,376
- [Karla] Oh.
- [in English] Hi, girls.

170
00:09:45,459 --> 00:09:48,546
- What are you doing here?
- The basketball court is far from here.

171
00:09:48,629 --> 00:09:50,339
[in English] Oh, I have something for you.

172
00:09:51,799 --> 00:09:53,134
[Gavin] That smells good now.
I had it laundered.

173
00:09:53,217 --> 00:09:54,302
[cheeky music playing]

174
00:09:54,385 --> 00:09:56,095
Are you saying I smell bad?

175
00:09:56,178 --> 00:09:58,139
[in English] Huh? I did not say anything.

176
00:09:58,222 --> 00:09:59,140
I did not say anything.

177
00:10:01,142 --> 00:10:02,226
[in English] Thank you.

178
00:10:03,102 --> 00:10:05,896
But if you had not taken it
from where I left it,

179
00:10:05,980 --> 00:10:07,481
I would have gotten it back
a long time ago.

180
00:10:08,232 --> 00:10:10,443
Thieves are not common in our area.

181
00:10:12,111 --> 00:10:13,696
[in English] Someone did steal
something from me.

182
00:10:15,114 --> 00:10:16,073
What is your friend saying?

183
00:10:16,782 --> 00:10:17,992
I do not know about that.

184
00:10:18,075 --> 00:10:20,369
Hey, Jason! What was stolen from you?

185
00:10:21,871 --> 00:10:22,830
[in English] My heart.

186
00:10:23,748 --> 00:10:24,957
[in English] She stole my heart.

187
00:10:28,377 --> 00:10:29,629
[in English] Hi, I am Jason.

188
00:10:34,258 --> 00:10:35,259
‪[sarcastic chuckle]

189
00:10:35,343 --> 00:10:40,139
Ah… I am taken. Yes, taken.
I am already taken.

190
00:10:40,222 --> 00:10:41,599
Ah, Karla, I will head back
to the shop first.

191
00:10:41,682 --> 00:10:45,102
Atoy might already be looking for me,
my love, so sweet.

192
00:10:45,186 --> 00:10:46,687
[Karla] All right.

193
00:10:46,771 --> 00:10:49,106
[cheeky music continues]

194
00:10:49,190 --> 00:10:53,110
Actually, that is the other reason
we are here.

195
00:10:53,194 --> 00:10:55,863
Jason has been pestering me
about your friend since last night.

196
00:10:55,946 --> 00:10:57,531
[in English] Is she really taken?

197
00:10:58,324 --> 00:11:00,409
Buddy, when a girl says she is taken,

198
00:11:00,493 --> 00:11:01,827
she is taken.

199
00:11:02,536 --> 00:11:05,790
So, what now?
You already did what you came here for.

200
00:11:05,873 --> 00:11:06,707
Are you leaving?

201
00:11:06,791 --> 00:11:09,168
No. Let us do something first.
Let us play. What?

202
00:11:09,251 --> 00:11:11,379
One game of 21.
We have clothes in the car.

203
00:11:11,462 --> 00:11:13,005
Hey, I am still busy. Next time.

204
00:11:13,089 --> 00:11:14,965
- You are busy?
- Yes.

205
00:11:16,133 --> 00:11:17,343
Do you have another trip with your boss?

206
00:11:17,426 --> 00:11:18,719
Where is your next adventure?

207
00:11:18,803 --> 00:11:20,554
Shh. You talk too much!

208
00:11:20,638 --> 00:11:22,139
Were you not told to stop talking so much?

209
00:11:24,642 --> 00:11:27,228
All right, I am leaving.

210
00:11:27,311 --> 00:11:28,396
Just a reminder…

211
00:11:29,355 --> 00:11:31,273
My boss gets very angry.

212
00:11:31,357 --> 00:11:35,820
[cheeky music continues]

213
00:11:39,949 --> 00:11:40,991
[in English] Guys!

214
00:11:41,075 --> 00:11:42,701
- [Kurt chuckles]
- [man] It is collection day again today.

215
00:11:42,785 --> 00:11:44,203
- Uh…
- [man] Well?

216
00:11:44,286 --> 00:11:47,164
I just paid two weeks ago, guys.

217
00:11:47,248 --> 00:11:51,335
And maybe not too often,
because how fast can I earn?

218
00:11:51,419 --> 00:11:55,339
You are in our territory,
so that is how it is.

219
00:11:56,090 --> 00:12:00,010
[man] If you do not want it,
then let us do this instead.

220
00:12:01,887 --> 00:12:02,763
[Kurt, in English] Guys, please!

221
00:12:02,847 --> 00:12:05,099
[brazen music playing]

222
00:12:05,182 --> 00:12:07,435
What? You really do not want to?

223
00:12:07,518 --> 00:12:11,105
[brazen music continues]

224
00:12:21,449 --> 00:12:23,701
[grunting]

225
00:12:23,784 --> 00:12:25,119
[screams]

226
00:12:25,202 --> 00:12:26,328
[Atoy] Is that okay?

227
00:12:26,412 --> 00:12:27,788
Let us add a bit more acid.

228
00:12:27,872 --> 00:12:28,873
Let us add some--

229
00:12:28,956 --> 00:12:32,543
- [man screaming]
- Wow!

230
00:12:32,626 --> 00:12:33,919
That feels good! Wow!

231
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:36,547
[grunting and groaning]

232
00:12:42,011 --> 00:12:43,846
‪[grunting and groaning]

233
00:12:43,929 --> 00:12:45,347
[man groaning]

234
00:12:46,724 --> 00:12:49,185
[man groaning]

235
00:12:52,146 --> 00:12:54,690
[suave music playing]

236
00:12:54,773 --> 00:12:56,108
Wait for our payback!

237
00:12:56,192 --> 00:12:57,943
- [man] We will come back for you!
- Oh, go ahead!

238
00:12:58,027 --> 00:13:00,821
- [Atoy] Go cry to your grandmother!
- [men grunting]

239
00:13:03,908 --> 00:13:05,451
- Brother Kurt, two more, please.
- Yes!

240
00:13:05,534 --> 00:13:06,869
[in English] Where did you learn
to do that?!

241
00:13:08,162 --> 00:13:09,371
Looks like your pares has some magic.

242
00:13:09,455 --> 00:13:11,373
[Atoy] Sorry about that.

243
00:13:11,457 --> 00:13:13,209
- Give me one more.
- [in English] Oh, wow!

244
00:13:13,292 --> 00:13:15,669
[in English] Thank you, okay?
My name is Kurt, by the way.

245
00:13:15,753 --> 00:13:18,214
- [in English] And what is your name?
- Atoy.

246
00:13:18,297 --> 00:13:20,132
[in English] Atoy? Nice to meet you.
Thank you, okay?

247
00:13:20,216 --> 00:13:21,091
Thank you very much.

248
00:13:21,675 --> 00:13:26,305
But, uh… Maybe I am not safe here anymore.

249
00:13:26,388 --> 00:13:27,973
They might come back for me.

250
00:13:28,557 --> 00:13:29,558
- Is that so?
- Maybe…

251
00:13:29,642 --> 00:13:30,559
[in English] I don't know.

252
00:13:30,643 --> 00:13:33,229
Maybe I should just close this business.

253
00:13:33,312 --> 00:13:35,523
You will close it? That would be a waste.

254
00:13:36,607 --> 00:13:37,942
- You know, Brother Kurt…
- [upbeat music playing]

255
00:13:38,692 --> 00:13:40,736
If you want, you can move to our barangay,

256
00:13:40,819 --> 00:13:42,196
Barangay Tabang Lupa.

257
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:45,616
I assure you, no one
will extort you there.

258
00:13:45,699 --> 00:13:47,284
I will endorse you to the barangay.

259
00:13:47,368 --> 00:13:50,496
If you are serious, just look
for it there. Then find the street.

260
00:13:50,579 --> 00:13:53,457
The street of Mr. Delfin's Tailoring.
I am there.

261
00:13:53,541 --> 00:13:55,209
- Oh, is that possible?
- You can be nearby.

262
00:13:55,292 --> 00:13:56,502
[in English] I would love that.
Thank you, yes.

263
00:13:56,585 --> 00:13:58,837
[in English] And I hope
you find Ibyang as well.

264
00:13:58,921 --> 00:14:00,422
- Thank you.
- [in English] Wow!

265
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:02,967
Just post it on your social media if ever.

266
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:04,260
[chuckles]

267
00:14:06,387 --> 00:14:09,056
Do you not have another spoon?
Because that jerk's blood is on this one.

268
00:14:17,648 --> 00:14:18,691
- Oh…
- [mid-tempo music playing]

269
00:14:20,234 --> 00:14:21,777
What? Did you find them?

270
00:14:21,861 --> 00:14:22,945
[in English] Negative.

271
00:14:27,616 --> 00:14:32,413
According to Ame's acquaintance,
they are from a province.

272
00:14:32,496 --> 00:14:34,206
They just do not know which province.

273
00:14:34,290 --> 00:14:35,666
They might have gone home.

274
00:14:37,334 --> 00:14:40,004
Oh, then why do you look sad?

275
00:14:40,087 --> 00:14:42,506
Did you not say you did not
want to see Ibyang?

276
00:14:42,590 --> 00:14:44,383
So, your wish already came true.

277
00:14:44,466 --> 00:14:46,176
That child is so annoying.

278
00:14:46,260 --> 00:14:48,679
You tell her off,
and she still doesn't listen.

279
00:14:48,762 --> 00:14:51,473
Just think, she cannot even reach
the sink, and yet she turns it on.

280
00:14:51,557 --> 00:14:53,517
She wants to wash the dish--
What if she slips?

281
00:14:53,601 --> 00:14:55,144
Right?

282
00:14:55,227 --> 00:14:56,520
Then the stove, she cannot even reach it.

283
00:14:56,604 --> 00:14:57,897
She turns it on, forcing herself to cook.

284
00:14:57,980 --> 00:14:59,064
What if she gets burned?

285
00:14:59,148 --> 00:15:01,859
Then at the bar,
she followed me to the bar.

286
00:15:01,942 --> 00:15:03,527
What if she gets kidnapped?

287
00:15:03,611 --> 00:15:04,737
Seriously…

288
00:15:05,446 --> 00:15:06,488
I really do not know about that kid.

289
00:15:06,572 --> 00:15:07,948
There it is…

290
00:15:08,032 --> 00:15:09,867
The truth finally came out.

291
00:15:09,950 --> 00:15:11,827
You are concerned about the child.

292
00:15:12,411 --> 00:15:13,787
You have grown attached to her, right?

293
00:15:14,914 --> 00:15:16,582
[scoffs] Wha--

294
00:15:17,499 --> 00:15:18,459
Attached? She is so annoying.

295
00:15:18,542 --> 00:15:20,419
- [Ibyang] Hey…
- If you see the--

296
00:15:20,502 --> 00:15:22,755
Master Grumpy loves me.

297
00:15:22,838 --> 00:15:26,133
[funky music playing]

298
00:15:29,178 --> 00:15:30,387
- Hey…
- [music ends]

299
00:15:32,890 --> 00:15:35,976
What-- What are you doing here?

300
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:38,604
Changing the subject.

301
00:15:38,687 --> 00:15:41,398
He does not want to admit
he cares about me.

302
00:15:41,482 --> 00:15:42,733
- Care care?
- [gentle music playing]

303
00:15:42,816 --> 00:15:45,152
What care, care, care, care?
You are annoying, care care?

304
00:15:45,235 --> 00:15:48,280
Oh, sorry, Atoy, that we came back.

305
00:15:48,364 --> 00:15:51,283
But we can leave
if you do not want us here.

306
00:15:53,077 --> 00:15:55,537
Hey, hey, hey, hey! No one is leaving.

307
00:15:55,621 --> 00:15:57,164
You and Ibyang will stay here.

308
00:15:57,247 --> 00:16:00,459
This is what will happen. Listen.

309
00:16:00,542 --> 00:16:03,087
They have nowhere to stay.

310
00:16:03,170 --> 00:16:06,924
You need someone to watch
the house when you are gone.

311
00:16:07,007 --> 00:16:09,343
It is a win-win situation for all of us.

312
00:16:10,678 --> 00:16:13,806
[chuckles, in English] Win-win situation…

313
00:16:13,889 --> 00:16:15,766
How do I win there?

314
00:16:15,849 --> 00:16:18,060
I can just lock the house when I leave.

315
00:16:18,727 --> 00:16:22,856
Ibyang and I will work
for our stay here, Atoy.

316
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:27,319
We will handle the cleaning
and all the housework.

317
00:16:27,403 --> 00:16:30,531
And we can also help
in your shop when needed.

318
00:16:31,448 --> 00:16:32,658
[Ibyang] Why "we"?

319
00:16:33,242 --> 00:16:34,451
Me too, Sis Ame?

320
00:16:35,327 --> 00:16:37,413
Of course, Ibyang.

321
00:16:37,496 --> 00:16:39,206
Everything must be earned.

322
00:16:40,290 --> 00:16:42,668
[bright music playing]

323
00:16:43,502 --> 00:16:44,336
‪[clears throat]

324
00:16:45,879 --> 00:16:47,006
Fine.

325
00:16:49,341 --> 00:16:50,467
But I do not want chaos.

326
00:16:54,054 --> 00:16:55,472
I do not want noise.

327
00:16:58,183 --> 00:16:59,476
I do not want annoying behavior.

328
00:17:01,395 --> 00:17:06,817
Oh. Then you might as well live
in the middle of the sea.

329
00:17:07,443 --> 00:17:11,947
There is nothing chaotic,
noisy, or annoying there.

330
00:17:12,031 --> 00:17:13,657
Ah… [chuckles sarcastically]

331
00:17:13,741 --> 00:17:16,744
And most of all,
I do not want smart mouths.

332
00:17:17,828 --> 00:17:20,122
[in English] Ah, okay, Atoy, okay.

333
00:17:21,665 --> 00:17:24,710
I promise you will have no problems
with me and Ibyang.

334
00:17:24,793 --> 00:17:26,086
[Cita chuckles]

335
00:17:26,170 --> 00:17:29,590
[bright music continues]

336
00:17:39,183 --> 00:17:42,227
Are you sure you are okay
staying here?

337
00:17:42,311 --> 00:17:43,228
[grunts]

338
00:17:43,312 --> 00:17:45,105
Oh, yes, of course.

339
00:17:45,189 --> 00:17:49,902
Ms. Cita, this is like a hotel
compared to where we stayed before.

340
00:17:50,736 --> 00:17:52,946
This house has an extra room.

341
00:17:53,030 --> 00:17:54,656
Why do you not sleep there?

342
00:17:55,324 --> 00:17:57,951
Uh… This is already
the best for us, Ms. Cita.

343
00:18:00,496 --> 00:18:02,372
We do not like rooms.

344
00:18:05,167 --> 00:18:06,251
[Cita] Ah…

345
00:18:08,087 --> 00:18:09,463
Here, this, this.

346
00:18:11,048 --> 00:18:12,174
[Cita] Mmm.

347
00:18:12,257 --> 00:18:15,928
[sentimental music playing]

348
00:18:51,797 --> 00:18:56,260
[Delfin] <i>When I am gone, do not</i>
<i>turn my room into a museum.</i>

349
00:18:57,010 --> 00:18:58,846
<i>You might not let anyone else use it.</i>

350
00:19:13,861 --> 00:19:19,491
[sentimental music continues]

351
00:19:57,696 --> 00:20:00,240
- Is it okay now?
- Here, take this too.

352
00:20:00,324 --> 00:20:02,242
- Fix it.
- Oh…

353
00:20:05,579 --> 00:20:07,539
I have been waiting for you to wake up.

354
00:20:08,999 --> 00:20:11,501
- You missed me already, Master?
- What "miss"?

355
00:20:12,211 --> 00:20:13,337
Get out of there already!

356
00:20:13,420 --> 00:20:15,047
You are making us leave already?

357
00:20:16,173 --> 00:20:17,758
I told you, Sis Ame,

358
00:20:18,467 --> 00:20:20,761
we should not expect anything.

359
00:20:20,844 --> 00:20:22,804
It turns out we were
only allowed one night.

360
00:20:23,388 --> 00:20:25,724
[scoffs] What are you talking about?

361
00:20:26,475 --> 00:20:28,685
What do you mean one night?

362
00:20:28,769 --> 00:20:32,648
What I am saying is,
there is a room there.

363
00:20:32,731 --> 00:20:35,609
No one is using it. You can use it.

364
00:20:35,692 --> 00:20:37,778
[sentimental music playing]

365
00:20:37,861 --> 00:20:38,904
Come on to your new room.

366
00:20:38,987 --> 00:20:43,116
He might still change his mind.
Come on! Come here, hurry!

367
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:44,368
Bring it along.

368
00:20:45,911 --> 00:20:48,789
Come on, hurry! Hurry!

369
00:20:50,332 --> 00:20:51,375
[Atoy grunts]

370
00:20:52,459 --> 00:20:54,544
[Ame and Ibyang giggling]

371
00:20:54,628 --> 00:20:55,879
Go on!

372
00:20:56,588 --> 00:21:00,175
I just do not want people
saying I am mistreating you.

373
00:21:03,262 --> 00:21:07,057
Hey… Looks like someone
felt industrious cleaning last night.

374
00:21:07,140 --> 00:21:09,226
Come in. Come on in.

375
00:21:09,309 --> 00:21:12,145
This used to be Atoy's father's room.

376
00:21:12,229 --> 00:21:13,855
It looks spacious enough. You will fit.

377
00:21:13,939 --> 00:21:17,567
Oh, wow, we really fit perfectly here!

378
00:21:17,651 --> 00:21:18,568
[Ibyang] Come here, quick.

379
00:21:19,194 --> 00:21:21,029
The bed is so soft!

380
00:21:21,113 --> 00:21:23,323
Try it, try it! Come here.

381
00:21:25,617 --> 00:21:29,288
A person was not made to live alone.

382
00:21:30,289 --> 00:21:32,624
Do you know what I want?

383
00:21:33,834 --> 00:21:36,044
I want you to have what we had

384
00:21:36,128 --> 00:21:38,046
when your mother was still alive.

385
00:21:39,131 --> 00:21:43,427
To have your own family

386
00:21:44,428 --> 00:21:46,888
that loves you

387
00:21:46,972 --> 00:21:48,140
and whom you will love.

388
00:21:48,223 --> 00:21:49,599
[sentimental music playing]

389
00:21:49,683 --> 00:21:50,809
- Oh…
- [Ibyang gasps]

390
00:21:51,476 --> 00:21:53,437
- [chuckles]
- [Ame] Oh, it is soft!

391
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:54,938
- It really is soft, right?
- [Ibyang] There is even a pillow.

392
00:21:55,022 --> 00:21:56,857
Brought a pillow along.
If you want, a blanket.

393
00:21:56,940 --> 00:21:59,067
Clean! Yay!

394
00:21:59,151 --> 00:22:00,444
Ame, do you not want to try it?

395
00:22:00,527 --> 00:22:02,654
[Ame] All right, maybe later.
Where will you be? There or here?

396
00:22:02,738 --> 00:22:04,406
- [Ibyang] Here.
- [Ame] All right, I will go there later.

397
00:22:04,990 --> 00:22:06,992
With all the places you have been to…

398
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:10,787
was there not even one woman

399
00:22:10,871 --> 00:22:12,789
who made your heart beat faster?

400
00:22:13,498 --> 00:22:14,666
Huh?

401
00:22:15,292 --> 00:22:17,669
[girls chuckling]

402
00:22:20,505 --> 00:22:22,007
[girls chuckling]

403
00:22:26,136 --> 00:22:31,683
[sentimental music continues]

404
00:22:33,643 --> 00:22:34,478
‪[gate screeches]

405
00:22:39,274 --> 00:22:45,489
[bright music playing]

406
00:22:55,082 --> 00:22:56,333
[in English] Welcome home, child!

407
00:22:57,375 --> 00:22:58,627
[in English] Thanks, Dad.

408
00:23:01,004 --> 00:23:02,089
[in English] Welcome back, sis.

409
00:23:03,507 --> 00:23:05,425
- [in English] Been a long time, brother.
- [in English] Yes, I know.

410
00:23:05,509 --> 00:23:08,345
[in English] Is it not too early
to be drinking?

411
00:23:08,428 --> 00:23:11,389
Dad, we just celebrated early
for your arrival.

412
00:23:12,140 --> 00:23:13,892
Hi. Hey!

413
00:23:13,975 --> 00:23:17,437
[in English] Audrey! Welcome back!

414
00:23:18,396 --> 00:23:20,315
[in English] Oh, love the perfume.

415
00:23:20,398 --> 00:23:22,567
Smells like an old cabinet.

416
00:23:22,651 --> 00:23:25,403
Hmm. Do you have a cold?

417
00:23:25,487 --> 00:23:27,531
[in English] It was made
by a perfumer in France.

418
00:23:27,614 --> 00:23:30,158
[in English] Must be
an expensive cabinet then.

419
00:23:31,201 --> 00:23:32,744
[in English] Welcome back, sis!

420
00:23:32,828 --> 00:23:35,122
[in English] Vacation, or what, for good?

421
00:23:36,331 --> 00:23:39,417
- [in English] We will see.
- [both chuckle pretentiously]

422
00:23:40,001 --> 00:23:41,837
[Dmitri, in English] Come on,
let us go inside. Everyone.

423
00:23:49,553 --> 00:23:54,266
[intense music playing]

424
00:23:55,767 --> 00:23:57,936
I already spoke to our contacts
at the cockpit, sir,

425
00:23:58,019 --> 00:24:00,188
and they said the one we are looking for

426
00:24:00,272 --> 00:24:02,065
has not shown up at the derby yet.

427
00:24:02,149 --> 00:24:04,860
Once I have a new lead, I will inform you.

428
00:24:04,943 --> 00:24:07,154
What could Master be busy with?

429
00:24:07,237 --> 00:24:08,321
[Ibyang] <i>Are there guns?</i>

430
00:24:08,405 --> 00:24:09,781
[Tonet] <i>What kind of rooster?</i>

431
00:24:09,865 --> 00:24:11,491
[Atoy] <i>I really need your help.</i>

432
00:24:11,575 --> 00:24:12,409
I need your expertise.

433
00:24:12,492 --> 00:24:13,869
No problem, Atoy! [scoffs]

434
00:24:13,952 --> 00:24:16,288
[in English] Anything
and everything for you.

435
00:24:16,371 --> 00:24:17,289
You have a strong pull with me.

436
00:24:17,372 --> 00:24:20,584
Atoy, maybe you will need my help too.
Just tell me.

437
00:24:20,667 --> 00:24:21,793
- Game?
- Mmm-hmm!

438
00:24:21,877 --> 00:24:23,295
They used to be your person, right?

439
00:24:23,378 --> 00:24:28,049
[chuckles] What is important
is that they complete the mission.

440
00:24:28,133 --> 00:24:31,469
[Mercado] <i>I am sure he will recover</i>
<i>your prized game cock.</i>

441
00:24:31,553 --> 00:24:32,971
[in English] Hi, kids!

442
00:24:33,054 --> 00:24:35,891
- [boy] Hi!
- Hi!

443
00:24:41,062 --> 00:24:43,648
‪Subtitle translation by: Judy Galleta
